# SPL grammar

## Lexical
	•	Identifiers: [A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*
	•	Strings: "..." (with escapes)
	•	Integers: decimal or hex 0x...
	•	Comments: # ... to end of line
	•	Newlines separate statements; blocks use { ... }

## Top-level

```
Program        := { ModuleItem } ;

ModuleItem     := ModuleDecl
               | ImportDecl
               | CapabilityDecl
               | TypeDecl
               | ErrorDecl
               | FnSpecDecl
               | LawDecl
               | ReqDecl
               | DecisionDecl
               | GenDecl
               | PropDecl
               | OracleDecl
               | PolicyDecl
               ;

ModuleDecl     := "module" QualifiedName ";" ;

ImportDecl     := "import" QualifiedName [ "as" Ident ] ";" ;

QualifiedName  := Ident { "." Ident } ;
Ident          := /[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*/ ;
String         := /"([^"\\]|\\.)*"/ ;
IntLit         := /0x[0-9A-Fa-f]+|[0-9]+/ ;
```

## Capabilities

```
CapabilityDecl := "capability" Ident "(" [ CapParams ] ")" ";" ;
CapParams      := CapParam { "," CapParam } ;
CapParam       := Ident ":" TypeRef ;
```

### Types

```
TypeDecl       := "type" Ident TypeBody ;
TypeBody       := AliasType
               | StructType
               | EnumType
               ;

AliasType      := "=" TypeRef [ RefineClause ] ";" ;

StructType     := "struct" "{" { FieldDecl } "}" [ InvariantBlock ] ";" ;
FieldDecl      := Ident ":" TypeRef ";" ;

EnumType       := "enum" "{" { VariantDecl } "}" ";" ;
VariantDecl    := Ident [ "(" [ VariantFields ] ")" ] ";" ;
VariantFields  := FieldType { "," FieldType } ;
FieldType      := TypeRef ;

TypeRef        := QualifiedName [ TypeArgs ] [ Nullability ] ;
TypeArgs       := "<" TypeRef { "," TypeRef } ">" ;
Nullability    := "?" ;

RefineClause   := "refine" RefineExpr ;
RefineExpr     := OrExpr ;
OrExpr         := AndExpr { "or" AndExpr } ;
AndExpr        := PredExpr { "and" PredExpr } ;
PredExpr       := CompareExpr | "(" RefineExpr ")" | "not" PredExpr ;
CompareExpr    := RefAtom (("=="|"!="|"<"|"<="|">"|">=") RefAtom)? ;
RefAtom        := "self" | Ident | IntLit | String | CallExpr ;
CallExpr       := Ident "(" [ ArgList ] ")" ;
ArgList        := RefAtom { "," RefAtom } ;

InvariantBlock := "invariant" "{" { RefineStmt } "}" ;
RefineStmt     := RefineExpr ";" ;
```

## Errors

```
ErrorDecl      := "error" Ident "{" { ErrorVariant } "}" ";" ;
ErrorVariant   := Ident ":" String ";" ;
```

## Function Specs

```
FnSpecDecl     := "fn" Ident FnHeader FnBlocks ";" ;

FnHeader       := "@id" "(" String ")"
                  [ "@compat" "(" CompatKind ")" ]
                  "(" [ Params ] ")"
                  "->" TypeRef
                  ;

CompatKind     := "stable_call" | "stable_semantics" | "unstable" ;

Params         := Param { "," Param } ;
Param          := Ident ":" TypeRef ;

FnBlocks       := "{" { FnBlock } "}" ;

FnBlock        := RequiresBlock
               | EnsuresBlock
               | EffectsBlock
               | ErrorsBlock
               | PerfBlock
               | ExamplesBlock
               | NotesBlock
               ;

RequiresBlock  := "requires" [ ReqTag ] BlockOfExpr ;
EnsuresBlock   := "ensures"  [ ReqTag ] BlockOfExpr ;

EffectsBlock   := "effects" "{" [ EffectList ] "}" ;
EffectList     := EffectItem { "," EffectItem } ;
EffectItem     := Ident "(" [ ArgList ] ")" | Ident ;

ErrorsBlock    := "raises" "{" { RaisesItem } "}" ;
RaisesItem     := QualifiedName [ ":" String ] ";" ;

PerfBlock      := "perf" "{" { PerfItem } "}" ;
PerfItem       := PerfKey ":" PerfValue ";" ;
PerfKey        := Ident ;
PerfValue      := String | IntLit | QualifiedName ;

ExamplesBlock  := "examples" [ ReqTag ] "{" { ExampleItem } "}" ;
ExampleItem    := String ":" ExampleExpr ";" ;
ExampleExpr    := Expr "==" Expr ;

NotesBlock     := "notes" "{" { NoteItem } "}" ;
NoteItem       := String ";" ;

BlockOfExpr    := "{" { RefineExpr ";" } "}" ;
```

## Optional laws/properties

```
LawDecl        := "law" Ident ":" RefineExpr ";" ;
```

You’ll notice SPL uses the same RefineExpr grammar for invariants/requirements/postconditions; it stays readable and small.
## Requirement declarations and traceability tags

Requirement IDs provide traceability from prose requirements to SPL clauses to generated tests.

```
ReqDecl        := "req" ReqId ":" String ";" ;
ReqId          := /REQ-[A-Za-z0-9_-]+/ ;

# Requirement tags can appear on requires/ensures/examples/props:
ReqTag         := "[" ReqId { "," ReqId } "]" ;
```

Requires/ensures/examples blocks can be tagged with `[REQ-…]` for traceability:
- `requires [REQ-12] { ... }` — links a precondition to a requirement
- `ensures [REQ-12] { ... }` — links a postcondition to a requirement
- `examples [REQ-13] { ... }` — links examples to a requirement

Tooling outputs:
- Which REQs are covered by examples/props
- Which are only prose (warning)
- Which code paths map to which REQs

## Decision declarations (must be resolved)

Decisions capture explicit tie-breakers and ambiguity resolutions. The compiler refuses to compile if any decision is unresolved.

```
DecisionDecl   := "decision" [ ReqTag ] Ident ":"
                  "when" ":" String ";"
                  "choose" ":" String ";"
                  ;
```

## Input generators (for property testing & fuzzing)

Generators define input domains for property testing and fuzz harness generation. They replace writing thousands of manual test cases.

```
GenDecl        := "gen" Ident "{" { GenField } "}" ";" ;
GenField       := GenKey ":" GenValue ";" ;
GenKey         := "charset" | "len" | "range" | "format" | "oneof" | "elements" | Ident ;
GenValue       := String | IntRange | Ident | "[" GenValueList "]" ;
GenValueList   := GenValue { "," GenValue } ;
IntRange       := IntLit ".." IntLit ;
```

## Property declarations (forall with shrinking)

Props are full property-based test declarations using `forall` quantification. They generate property tests and can include shrinking hints.

```
PropDecl       := "prop" [ ReqTag ] Ident ":"
                  { PropQuantifier }
                  PropBody ";" ;

PropQuantifier := "forall" Ident ":" TypeRef [ "from" Ident ] ;
PropBody       := RefineExpr ;
```

The `from` clause references a `gen` declaration for the domain. If omitted, the type's default generator is used.

## Oracle declarations (reference/optimized linkage)

Oracles allow marking a function as having a reference implementation. The agent first produces a simple correct reference, then an optimized version; differential tests run between them.

```
OracleDecl     := "oracle" QualifiedName ":" OracleKind ";" ;
OracleKind     := "reference" | "optimized" ;
```

## Package-level policy

Policy declarations restrict what effects/capabilities modules may use. They serve as acceptance gates ensuring the agent doesn't perform unexpected I/O.

```
PolicyDecl     := "policy" "{" { PolicyRule } "}" ";" ;
PolicyRule     := PolicyAllow | PolicyDeny | PolicyDeterminism ;
PolicyAllow    := "allow" Ident [ "(" PolicyConstraint ")" ] ";" ;
PolicyDeny     := "deny" Ident ";" ;
PolicyDeterminism := "deterministic" ";" ;
PolicyConstraint  := Ident ":" PolicyValue { "," Ident ":" PolicyValue } ;
PolicyValue       := String | "[" StringList "]" ;
StringList        := String { "," String } ;
```

## Example

```
module music.scale;

# Requirement traceability
req REQ-1: "Notes must be in range 1..12";
req REQ-2: "Snap result must be in the scale";
req REQ-3: "Tie-break chooses smaller numeric note";

type MidiNote = Int refine (1 <= self and self <= 12);

# Input generator for property testing
gen MidiNoteGen {
  range: 1..12;
};

gen ScaleGen {
  elements: MidiNoteGen;
  len: 1..12;
};

# Explicit decision for tie-break ambiguity
decision [REQ-3] tie_break:
  when: "multiple notes at equal minimum distance";
  choose: "the smaller numeric note";

fn snap_to_scale @id("music.snap.v1") @compat(stable_semantics)
  (note: MidiNote, scale: Set<MidiNote>) -> MidiNote
{
  requires [REQ-2] { scale_is_nonempty(scale); }
  ensures  [REQ-2] { set_contains(scale, result); }
  notes {
    "Distance is circular over 12. Tie-break chooses smaller numeric note.";
  }
  perf {
    time: "O(|scale|)";
    alloc: "none";
  }
  examples [REQ-3] {
    "octave edge goes to 1, not 0": snap_to_scale(12, {1,5,8}) == 1;
    "already in scale":            snap_to_scale(1,  {1,5,8}) == 1;
  }
};

# Property with forall quantification
prop [REQ-2] snap_in_scale:
  forall n: MidiNote from MidiNoteGen
  forall s: Set<MidiNote> from ScaleGen
  set_contains(s, snap_to_scale(n, s));

# Idempotence property
prop snap_idempotent:
  forall n: MidiNote from MidiNoteGen
  forall s: Set<MidiNote> from ScaleGen
  snap_to_scale(snap_to_scale(n, s), s) == snap_to_scale(n, s);

# Oracle: mark the reference implementation
oracle music.scale.snap_to_scale: reference;

# Package-level policy
policy {
  deny Net;
  deny FileWrite;
  deterministic;
};
```

